   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1838_04_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1838-04-06">May 10<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1838</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName>To <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF3">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Wilson</persName>
                  </persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
               I received this letter<lb/>
               this morning with <persName ref="./Personography.xml#KnigW1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. W Knightons</persName>
               <lb/>
               <title ref="./Workography.xml#Memoi10">Book</title> - It had<lb/>
               been lying <unclear>at</unclear>
               <lb/>
               the <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Dublin_IE">Dublin</placeName> book<lb/>
               sellers or somewhere<lb/>
               a month you see<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               In <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WilsL1">Lestocks</persName>
               <lb/>
               last letter he told<lb/>
               me that <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BentR1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Bentley</persName>
               <lb/>
               would write to<lb/>
               me in consequence<lb/>
               of the agreement he<lb/>
               had made with him<lb/>
               and would put<lb/>
               that agreement in<lb/>
               his letter in the<lb/>
               form of a proposal<lb/>
               which I was of course<lb/>
               to accept in consequence<lb/>
               of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WilsL1">Lestocks</persName> agreement<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               But I have never heard from <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BentR1">Bentley</persName>
               <lb/>
               <hi rend="underline">This</hi> letter you<lb/>
               see is previous to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WilsL1">Lestocks</persName>
               <lb/>
               which is date the 23<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> april<lb/>
               I send a note to Bentley which I beg you to forward to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WilsL1">Lestock</persName>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1838_04_page02.jpg"/>
               as I wish the whole to go<lb/>
               through her hands<lb/>
               You ask how I came by<lb/>
               my new pretty letter <hi rend="underline">Maria</hi>
               <lb/>
               seal - <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MoorG1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. George Moore</persName> gave<lb/>
               it to me with a very nice little<lb/>
               pencil case with screw in &amp; out<lb/>
               pencils.<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> ever &amp; ever<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria E</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
